ce:section.ce:para:
Infrared spectroscopy (FT-IR) was used to investigate the functional groups of synthesized GQD. The FT-IR spectrum of GQD is given in Fig. 1
                        . In the corresponding range, the peaks of the 3400 cm−1 region are describes to the OH group. Also, the peaks observed in 1380 and 1600 cm−1 are related to CO and CO. The X-ray diffraction (XRD) pattern of GQD can be seen at θ2 = 24° relates to plate (002) which corresponds to card number JCDS-0024 (Fig. 2
                        ). This broad peak observed is due to the amorphous nature of GQD.
